.TH INFINITETUX 6
.SH NAME
infinitetux \- retro 2D platformer with procedurally generated levels (native SDL2 edition)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B infinitetux
.RI [ options ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B Infinite Tux
is a C++ port of the original Java platformer, built on SDL2 with full gamepad support.
It is inspired by Markus "Notch" Persson's public-domain
\fIInfinite Mario Bros.\fR, re-themed with Tux and free assets.
Each run generates new levels, so playthroughs vary even with the same settings.
.PP
The game ships with system-wide assets under
.IR /usr/share/games/infinitetux/ ,
and can optionally load override assets from the per-user data directory (see
.BR FILES ).
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Show a help/usage summary and exit.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-debug
Enable debug output (for example, spawn messages and collision information).
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-test
Enable test mode (see
.BR "TEST MODE" ).
.TP
.BR \-\-default
Use the default input bindings and ignore any saved bindings/configuration.
Use this if custom bindings become unusable.
.SH CONTROLS
.SS Gameplay
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Move left/right; climb vines; duck (Down).
.TP
.BR A " / " Z
Jump (hold longer to jump higher).
.TP
.BR S " / " X
Run (hold while moving); shoot fireballs; pick up/hold shells (hold while stomping).
.TP
.B Enter
Pause/unpause.
.TP
.B Escape
Quit.
.TP
.B F9
Cycle MIDI synth backend (Default/Native/FluidSynth), if available.
.TP
.B F10
Cycle scale quality (Nearest/Linear/Best).
.TP
.B F11
Toggle fullscreen.
.SS Menus
.TP
.B Arrow keys
Navigate menu options.
.TP
.BR A " / " Z " / " Enter
Select the current option.
.SS Gamepad
Gamepads are automatically detected. Configure bindings via the Options menu.
.TP
.B D-pad / Left Stick
Move; navigate menus.
.TP
.B A button
Jump; select.
.TP
.B B / X button
Run; fire; back.
.TP
.B Start
Pause.
.SH TEST MODE
Test mode is intended for development and level experimentation:
.IP \(bu 2
The player is invincible (toggle with the backtick key \fB`\fR).
.IP \(bu 2
Time does not run out.
.IP \(bu 2
Debug messages are enabled.
.IP \(bu 2
A special test map provides access to all level types.
.PP
Additional test keys:
.TP
.B I
Make the player small.
.TP
.B O
Make the player big.
.TP
.B P
Give fire power.
.TP
.BR 0 \- 9
Spawn an enemy at the player's position:
0=Goomba, 1=Green Koopa, 2=Red Koopa, 3=Spiky,
4=Winged Goomba, 5=Winged Green Koopa,
6=Winged Red Koopa, 7=Winged Spiky,
8=Shell, 9=Bullet Bill.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I /usr/share/games/infinitetux/
System-wide game data installed by the package (read-only).
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/infinitetux/
Per-user data directory (created on first run if needed). Used for saved settings
and optional per-user asset overrides. If
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
is set, the directory is instead:
.IR $XDG_DATA_HOME/infinitetux/ .
